# Ability Name	Unique Key					Category of Ability		Type						Define				Description																																																																																																																Modify VAR																	Source Page		Aspects
Poison		KEY:Poison ~ Leng Spider		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural	DEFINE:LengSpiderPoisonDC|0	DESC:Bite - injury; save Fort DC %1; frequency 1/round for 6 rounds; effect 1d4 Con plus confusion for 1 round; cure 2 consecutive saves.  A Leng spider's venom causes flesh to blister and rot away and the mind to experience vivid and horrific hallucinations - these visions cause the poisoned creature to react in an unpredictable manner, as if confused.  The hallucination element of this poison is mind-affecting.|LengSpiderPoisonDC																																									BONUS:VAR|LengSpiderPoisonDC|10+TL/2+CON	BONUS:VAR|LengSpiderPoisonDC|2|PREFEAT:1,Ability Focus (Poison)	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	ASPECT:Ability Benefit|(bite)
Web Weaponry	KEY:Web Weaponry ~ Leng Spider	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary						DESC:A Leng spider is talented at using its webs to construct masterwork weapons.  This technique of weapon creation allows the spider to effectively create a flail or bolas by attaching a heavy object such as a rock or chunk of metal to a cord of webbing.  The spider attaches one end of this webbing to a leg and can then wield the weighted cords as a masterwork flail or a massterwork bolas.  It can only wield one such weapon at a time - it must use its other legs to walk.  If a Leng spider drops or loses a web weapon, it can create a new one as a full-round action, provided it has access to heavy-weight objects of the correct size (such as loose rocks or skulls).																			SOURCEPAGE:p.176

